textDelta: Theories that are grand are like skyscrapers that need to be rooted in a solid foundation.
If a theory crumbles like an old building, then it just means there must have been holes somewhere on the supporting levels.
Buildings, like theories, need inspection from time to time to make sure things are safe and running smoothly.
